{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mental health care: Right to request female observer, fund staff & training",
        "additional_details": "We ask the Government to:\r\nEnforce policy across all mental health settings giving female patients the statutory right to request female 1:1 staff\r\nProvide funding to ensure safe, gender-appropriate staffing levels.\r\nFund trauma-informed and gender-sensitive care training for all staff in mental health wards\r\n \r\nWe think these changes would protect vulnerable patients, improve recovery outcomes, and ensure safer, more respectful environments in mental health settings.",
        "background": "We think the Government should require all NHS and mental health care providers to give female patients the statutory right to request female-only 1:1 (constant) staff observations when detained under the Mental Health Act or receiving inpatient care on a psychiatric ward.",
